<h3 id="overview">Overview</h3>
<p>
    <code>CustomTranslationProvider</code> is the single contract every translation provider implements.
    Its one method, <code>resolve()</code>, receives a message key and the active locale, and returns
    either a <code>MessageFn</code> — a function that formats the message with the given parameters — or
    <code>null</code> to decline and let resolution continue down the locale fallback chain and on to the
    next registered provider. A native <code>Intl</code> MessageFormat 2.0 formatter, lazy-namespace
    catalogs, and library adapters (FormatJS, i18next, Lingui, Paraglide) all satisfy this same
    interface, which is what lets <a href="/plugs/customtranslationproviderregistry/">the registry</a>
    treat them interchangeably.
</p>

